Reasoning: The paper deals with pilot signal design for massive MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The optimization problem involved in the pilot design is a convex optimization problem, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method in terms of received SNR, which is a metric related to signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on massive MIMO systems, which is a subfield of wireless communication (cs.MM).
